From Ronald van Loon Subject Announcing the Motif mailing list I am glad and proud to announce the new mailing list for the PD Motif C I got over replies in about one week of people interested in such a list and the software has now been properly installed so the list is now up and For those interested in joining please send e mail to that extend to 'motif ' or '' The blurb everyone who joins gets follows as well as the original announcement for where Motif can be Enjoy Welcome to the Motif Mailing List The Motif mailing list is a mailing list dedicated to Motif the PD C wrapper library for Motif where people can ask questions about Motif swap stories and give new ideas about new directions and improvements for the All requests of an administrative nature like subscription removal should be directed to motif All e mail sent to motif will be sent to the entire list so please make sure when using 'vacation' type programs that will reply to messages automatically that the address for the mailing list is excluded from auto Enjoy Ronald van Loon In theory there is no difference between theory and Group Utrecht The Netherlands In practice however there Hello Motif World over the past half year there have been a lot of relatively minor changes to the Motif Imake support has been improved a few defaults have been changed and a lot of other small things have been This is basically a release which drops the 'gamma' Next release will incorporate some improvements by Stefan Schwarz and possibly will support and Motif Note to all of those who keep copies of the archive please retrieve this distribution during off peak hours and delete all previous Here is the original ANNOUNCEMENT HISTORY The University of Lowell supported by a grant of the Open Software Foundation has developed a wrapper library that encapsulates Motif widgets in C All resources of these Widgets can now be set through member functions while objects can be used in callback The library was made available for free or nominal cost for anonymous ftp at However the library contained a large number of bugs and oversights and only worked under Due to lack of subsequent fundings the bindings are no longer actively supported by the University of I Ronald van Loon at a certain point last year have taken the Lowell bindings fixing the bugs I came across adding missing memberfunctions and enhancing functionality and made the bug fixed library available for the general public for anonymous ftp made possible by Rick Murphy at DEC NEW RELEASE I am now pleased to announce a new and updated release of the Motif This release offers Full and support Support for Xbae widgetset Two additional widgets written by myself that can be used to indicate progress in an Imake NB this release relies heavily on the existence of imake and its config files on your I have tried to provide the bindings with a standard Makefile tweakable for those unfortunates without I have not severely tested the standard Makefile Contact me if you have The reason for calling this a gamma release lies in the fact that I do not have a multitude of platforms to test the Imake files Lots of testfiles even somewhat useful programs An article I wrote on the usage of Motif X and C previously posted on WHERE TO GET THE NEW MOTIF BINDINGS Ftp Anonymous ftp at directory pub Note Please be patient as the network link is quite Please do not FTP large files during working Also note that there is also a motif file at this site this is an old version of the E mail Those who don't have ftp can send me e mail and I will send the bindings by e REQUEST Those who use the bindings and find bugs or see room for improvement please contact me and I will try to incorporate them in a future release in case of bugs a bug fix of course MORE INFORMATION Contact me at If you are desperate then you can call me at that is Utrecht the Netherlands those within the Netherlands call Enjoy Ronald van Loon In theory there is no difference between theory and Group Utrecht The Netherlands In practice however there